Rating: 4
I made this pretty much as directed (proportions of a few things may have been off because I'm a guesstimator cook), but I made a large batch because I had a *huge* eggplant from my CSA. This was fabulous, quick, and simple. The eggplant texture holds up to the parsley and oil mixture, the flavor is fantastic and bright, and (even better) it keeps well in the fridge and I'm enjoying it a week later! As a bonus, the parsley mixture is also a fantastic chicken (and probably beef and fish) marinade. I marinated chicken breasts in it for about 15 minutes, then grilled and they were flavorful and tender. I'll definitely make this again!

Rating: 4
